=head1 DESCRIPTION

A structure describing the configuration and details of a storage
optimizer.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Config => L<Paws::LakeFormation::StorageOptimizerConfig>

A map of the storage optimizer configuration. Currently contains only
one key-value pair: C<is_enabled> indicates true or false for
acceleration.


=head2 ErrorMessage => Str

A message that contains information about any error (if present).

When an acceleration result has an enabled status, the error message is
empty.

When an acceleration result has a disabled status, the message
describes an error or simply indicates "disabled by the user".


=head2 LastRunDetails => Str

When an acceleration result has an enabled status, contains the details
of the last job run.


=head2 StorageOptimizerType => Str

The specific type of storage optimizer. The supported value is
C<compaction>.


